From e3b86f4e558cea9eed71d894df2f19b10d60a207 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Corentin Labbe <clabbe@baylibre.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Dec 2021 17:16:32 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] media: staging: media: zoran: calculate the right buffer
 number for zoran_reap_stat_com
Git-commit: e3b86f4e558cea9eed71d894df2f19b10d60a207
Patch-mainline: v5.18-rc1
References: CVE-2021-47645 bsc#1237767

mhocko@suse.com:
partial backport due to missing 83f89a8bcbc3c

On the case tmp_dcim=1, the index of buffer is miscalculated.
This generate a NULL pointer dereference later.

So let's fix the calcul and add a check to prevent this to reappear.

Signed-off-by: Corentin Labbe <clabbe@baylibre.com>
Signed-off-by: Hans Verkuil <hverkuil-cisco@xs4all.nl>
Signed-off-by: Mauro Carvalho Chehab <mchehab@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Michal Hocko <mhocko@suse.com>

---
 drivers/media/pci/zoran/zoran_device.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/media/pci/zoran/zoran_device.c
+++ b/drivers/media/pci/zoran/zoran_device.c
@@ -1142,7 +1142,7 @@ zoran_reap_stat_com (struct zoran *zr)
 			     zr->jpg_err_shift) & BUZ_MASK_STAT_COM;
 		else
 			i = ((zr->jpg_dma_tail -
-			      zr->jpg_err_shift) & 1) * 2 + 1;
+			      zr->jpg_err_shift) & 1) * 2;
 
 		stat_com = le32_to_cpu(zr->stat_com[i]);
 
